[16:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one video rapper, for suggesting this. What you need to do is go in Comfy UI and then in Comfy and then look for LDM and then lights and then look for this embeddings connector.py file. Now, you'

[16:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can rightclick and either edit this in Notepad or whatever text editor you want. For me, I\'m going to open this up in VS Code. So, here\'s what the file looks like. And you can press Ctrl+F to search for hidden'

[16:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'states and then equals torch. And you should see this line. What you need to do is replace this line and paste in this new line which looks like this. I\'ll add this line of code in the'

[16:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description or a pinned comment. So, you can just copy and paste it into here. Afterwards, simply press Ctrl S to save this file. And just by doing this, it should help you fit LTX2 with even lower VRAM. Here\'s another tip. Here\'s the'

[17:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'file which you would use to start up Comi. So, what you can do is rightclick on this and then click on edit in Notepad. And you should see something like this. The last line here should be something like this. Now, if you have'

[17:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'low VRAM, what you could do is add a parameter called d--reserve-v. And then you would add a number, let\'s say four. And what this means is it\'s going to always keep 4 GB of VRAM free.'

[17:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And this prevents Windows or other apps from fighting Comfy UI for VRAM. And it\'s going to offload everything else to your computer\'s RAM. Now, if you have even lower VRAM, let\'s say under 4 GB,'

[17:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then instead of just reserve VRAM, what you could do is to write dash- no VRAM, which is going to force all offloading of your models into your RAM. So, again, you\'re going to need like over 30ome GB'

[18:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of RAM in order for you to fit everything. But if you do have that much RAM, then you\'ll still be able to use LTX2 using this method. So, afterwards, just press Ctrl S to save this file. And then you can open up Comfy UI again and'

